  "special": {
    "title": "Torgue got more BOOM!",
    "description": "Each rocket explodes on impact and then drops a child grenade that detonates shortly afterward. The child grenade scales with grenade damage bonuses. The weapon cannot score critical hits."
  },
  "notes": "Point-blank shots can damage you and nearby allies with both the main rocket and the child grenade. Under the Grog Nozzle drunk effect, it can fire six rockets at once, with each rocket spawning its own grenade. Kills count for Pull the Pin. Absorb shields can absorb the main rocket as launcher ammo, but not the child grenade, and amp shields boost both parts of the shot. Grenade damage bonuses increase the child grenade's damage. It works especially well with explosive-focused builds, but it is a poor fit for high-Anarchy Gaige because the rockets do not benefit from Close Enough and the spread makes self-hits more likely.",
